Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: i know absolutely nothing about Pirate

Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: id appreciate if someone could tell me what it is, where/why to buy

Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: etc.

Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: whats its purpose and advantages

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: zcash has this problem: https://cryptolux.org/images/d/d9/Zcash.pdf

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: PIRATE is the solution

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: total privacy

Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: so if a wallet ID is hidden, does that mean you can't see transactions on the ledger?\

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: all that can be seen is a txid, that says that someone sent some amount to somebody

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: without any other details

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: like this: http://pirate.explorer.dexstats.info/tx/543455eb9e52a0ffb57ddbbb149edf2dfd5fe67d4eeddeb0c4451c546f18f35b

Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: aah

Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: and so the issue with zcash is that these transactions can be traced from a private address to a public one, thus  deanonymizing the users?

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the problem with zcash is only about 15% of tx are shielded, so the rest are fully transparent, which has 2 effects

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: 1) no privacy at all for 85%

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: 2) privacy for the 15% is mostly lost

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: this is because most of the private tx are miners shielding coinbase (this is a requirement for zcash) and then immediately convert to transparent to deposit and sell to exchange

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: optional privacy ends up being no privacy at all

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: with PIRATE it is 100% privacy for user tx, and there is no option, so users cant even mess up their privacy short of posting "hey i just did a txid for 400 PIRATE"

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: with a mixed taddr/zaddr setup it is very easy to lose all the privacy by sending some funds to an address that is correlated externally

Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: i see

Author: FlyingDutchman#5213
Content: thank you very much

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: and mixers cant be trusted: https://news.bitcoin.com/dont-trust-bitcoin-mixers-and-other-opsec-lessons-from-the-darknet/

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so I am recommending PIRATE for anybody that wants the most privacy
